---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
	title="Online Ruler Accuracy Guide"
	description="Learn how online ruler accuracy works, why browser zoom matters, and how to get better physical measurements from your screen."
	canonicalPath="/accuracy-guide/"
>
	<main id="main">
		<section class="accuracy-band px-spacing-md py-spacing-5xl md:px-spacing-lg">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl">
				<p class="mb-spacing-sm font-mono text-xs text-white/60">accuracy guide</p>
				<h1 class="max-w-3xl text-balance text-5xl font-semibold leading-tight tracking-normal">Make Screen Measurements More Reliable.</h1>
				<p class="mt-spacing-md max-w-2xl text-lg leading-8 text-white/70">
					An online ruler can be useful for quick measurements, but physical accuracy depends on calibration, screen density, browser zoom, and display scaling.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="bg-canvas px-spacing-md py-spacing-4xl md:px-spacing-lg">
			<div class="mx-auto grid max-w-5xl gap-spacing-lg">
				<article class="card-marketing">
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-normal">Keep Browser Zoom At 100%.</h2>
					<p class="mt-spacing-sm text-body">
						Zoom changes how CSS pixels are mapped to the display. Calibrate and measure at 100% zoom when exact size matters.
					</p>
				</article>
				<article class="card-marketing">
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-normal">Use A Physical Reference.</h2>
					<p class="mt-spacing-sm text-body">
						Credit card calibration is practical because it compares the ruler to a real object with a standard width of 85.60 mm.
					</p>
				</article>
				<article class="card-marketing">
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-normal">Recalibrate When Displays Change.</h2>
					<p class="mt-spacing-sm text-body">
						External monitors, display scaling, and operating-system settings can change the physical result. Save a fresh calibration for each screen.
					</p>
				</article>
			</div>
		</section>
	</main>
</BaseLayout>
